10 Hours Ago The defendants, in the counts, were accused of conspiracy to launder funds obtained through unlawful activity, retention of such funds, transfer of funds for a suspect, Olayinka Jimoh popularly known as Nappy Boy, and unlawful transfer of funds for a record label, among others. Mompha pleaded not guilty to the charges on behalf of his company. However, after entertaining submission of the counsel, Justice Dada ordered his remand in the custody of the EFCC till January 18 when his bail application will be heard.